A) APPROVE

Page Web
http://aprove.informatik.rwth-aachen.de/index.asp?subform=download.html

Choix de la version non-Eclipse

wget http://aprove.informatik.rwth-aachen.de/downloads/cli/aprove.jar

B) Dependances

  1) Il faut OpenJDK 1.8 : install√© dans $HOME/jdk1.8.0_101

  2) Il faut MiniSat :
	apt-get install minisat2

  3) Il faut Yices 1 (not Yices 2)

"AProVE works with Yices 1 (e.g., Yices 1.0.40 released December 4, 2013)
but not Yices 2. Please download Yices 1 from 
http://yices.csl.sri.com/old/download-yices1.shtml.
After extracting the files, please make sure to add the yices bin 
sub-directory (e.g. C:\Program Files\yices-1.0.40\bin\ or 
/home/username/yices-1.0.40/bin/) to your path environment as described 
below, and make sure that this sub-directory appears before any other
directory (e.g., /usr/local/bin) that would also contain a yices binary,
yet in version 2".

http://yices.csl.sri.com/old/download-yices1-full.shtml

choose the statically linked binaries

 yices-1.0.40-i686-pc-linux-gnu-static-gmp.tar.gz
 yices-1.0.40-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu-static-gmp.tar.gz

cd APROVE/
tar xvf yices-1.0.40-i686-pc-linux-gnu-static-gmp.tar.gz


